{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2025-1978","published":"2025-08-08T11:16:38Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:31:10.884629Z","upstream":["CVE-2024-13978"],"summary":"libtiff security update","details":"This  provides support for the Tag Image File Format (TIFF), a widely used format for storing image data. The latest version of the TIFF specification is available on-line in several different formats.And contains command-line programs for manipulating TIFF format image files using the libtiff library.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nA vulnerability was found in LibTIFF up to 4.7.0. It has been declared as problematic. Affected by this vulnerability is the function t2p_read_tiff_init of the file tools/tiff2pdf.c of the component fax2ps. The manipulation leads to null pointer dereference. The attack needs to be approached locally. The complexity of an attack is rather high. The exploitation appears to be difficult. The patch is named 2ebfffb0e8836bfb1cd7d85c059cd285c59761a4. It is recommended to apply a patch to fix this issue.(CVE-2024-13978)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"libtiff","ecosystem":"openEuler:22.03-LTS-SP4","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/libtiff&distro=openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["libtiff-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.aarch64.rpm","libtiff-debuginfo-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.aarch64.rpm","libtiff-debugsource-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.aarch64.rpm","libtiff-devel-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.aarch64.rpm","libtiff-static-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.aarch64.rpm","libtiff-tools-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["libtiff-help-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.noarch.rpm"],"src":["libtiff-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["libtiff-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.x86_64.rpm","libtiff-debuginfo-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.x86_64.rpm","libtiff-debugsource-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.x86_64.rpm","libtiff-devel-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.x86_64.rpm","libtiff-static-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.x86_64.rpm","libtiff-tools-4.3.0-40.oe2203sp4.x86_64.